 video has expired.  Read the full article here  After Germany appeared to be stiff competition at the start of the game, the U.S. women's basketball team remembered who they were in the second quarter.  The U.S. hit their stride with a sharp 11-0 run fueled by improved shooting and more aggression in the paint. But the team still has room for cohesion, and they might be lucky that Germany's 3-pointers went cold.  After a sluggish start, A'ja Wilson found her form again, combining for 19 points with Breanna Stewart.  Germany set the tone early, with three consecutive shots from downtown to continue their strong 3-point shooting in Paris so far. The U.S. continued to struggle with theirs, missing all three of their attempts in the first quarter.  Breanna Stewart leads the U.S. in scoring with 6 points.  Did Suni Lee think she would be here at Paris 2024 given her recent battles with kidney disease?  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAbsolutely not,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIn the back of my head, I really thought that I was done.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Gymnastics \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even something that I wanted to do anymore. I was ready to move on with my life. I wanted to move across the country, and everyone\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s like, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098What are you talking about? Like you can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t make decisions when you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re sad,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she added with a laugh.  The result, however, is a Games where she and her fellow Team USA gymnasts are clearly in a better place than at Tokyo 2020. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou could look back and see a lot of the girls not really having a lot of fun and not smiling,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd this time we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re celebrating after every turn, going up and hugging everybody.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Beaming, she said that \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cgymnastics is a lot more fun when you\